==Trivia==
* Ugochukwu's native chieftaincy title is: ''<U+201C>Aha Eji Agamba<U+201D>'', [[igbo language|Igbo]] for ''"he who gives the community cause to boast"'' [http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/columnists/bottomline/bottomline-june12-2005.htm][http://www.newabia.com/the_candidate.html].

* Ugochukwu was mentioned as part of a ''[[Saturday Night Live|Saturday Night Live (SNL)]]'' skit mocking the 2000 United States presidential debate between [[Al Gore]] and [[George W Bush]]. Bush (played by [[Will Ferrell]]), attempts to prove his competence in [[foreign affairs]] as he discusses the [[Government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]]: ''"Jim, I got some more Nigerian names for ya. Chief Onyema Ugochukwu, Special Assistant to the President on National Orientation and Public Affairs"'' [http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lKCVlxbTync].
* The ''Onyema Ugochukwu Auditorium'' in the [[University of Uyo]] is named for Ugochukwu[http://www.uniuyo.edu.ng/UNIUYO-project.htm].

